{
  "stem": "1282.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But if it were the closest thing to what my father did, he was sort of like the mayor of the town.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "All the official documents, he signed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "All the official papers came through him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And Mr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Basch was looked upon as the man who knows all the answers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So yes, we were an important family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The village-- most people spoke a Ukrainian dialect, Ruthenian Ukrainian dialect.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, there were some that, not so much the children, as the parents, spoke Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because remember, they were older, and they were from Hungary-Austria time, so they still spoke Hungarians, few.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most Jews spoke Yiddish, Ukrainian, and Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have had to learn, when I was born, Hungarian to communicate with the maid.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then I immediately, at age of three, thee and a half, we started going to cheder, which was the name for the Hebrew school, studying the Yiddish, or the Hebrew, the Torah.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there I had to learn the Hebrew and the Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then at home, we also spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then I went to public school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I had to speak the Ukrainian, which was a Ruthenian language.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that made it immediately three languages.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Then later on, it was compulsory to learn at least the basics of Czech because Czechoslovakia was the country that controlled it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So simultaneously, by the age of six or so, I spoke Hungarian, Yiddish, Ivrit, really, more than Hebrew, Ukrainian, and some Czech.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They spoke all those languages.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, at home, we used to-- we used either Yiddish or Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We did not use the Ukrainian language because we never felt comfortable.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was not our language.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was something we had to do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, the Jewish familiar were-- at least, they were always literate in the Hebrew and in the Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
